UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426682800101
AB  - This paper examines the implications of Euromarket regulation on the balance sheet decisions of an international bank. A model of an international bank with strong neoclassical microeconomic roots is developed. The model is then used to analyze the effects of two different techniques for Euromarket regulation, reserve requirements and capital/asset ratios. Among the conclusions to emerge from the paper is that reserve requirements in the Euromarkets will affect only the bank's international operations, but capital/asset ratios will affect domestic operations as well. The effect of capital/asset ratios on domestic operations may well be larger than on international operations.
